  "instructions": [
    "in a mortar and pestle, pound the garlic, ginger, and cayenne pepper until well combined.",
    "heat the duck fat in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "add the onions and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "add the fennel seeds and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "add the white wine and cook until almost completely reduced, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom of the pan.",
    "add the duck stock and bring to a simmer.",
    "reduce heat to low and let cook for 10 minutes.",
    "stir in the heavy cream and let cook for 2-3 minutes, or until heated through.",
    "season with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "stir in the fresh parsley and serve hot."
